<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-16361] DROP COMPACT STORAGE should invalidate prepared statements still using CompactTableMetadata</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16361</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we drop compact storage from a table, existing prepared statements continue to refer to an instance of &lt;tt&gt;CompactTableMetadata&lt;/tt&gt;, rather than being invalidated so they can be assigned a new &lt;tt&gt;TableMetadata&lt;/tt&gt; instance. There are perhaps some brute force ways to fix this, like bouncing the node, but that obviously sub-optimal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One idea is to have &lt;tt&gt;TableMetadata#changeAffectsPreparedStatements()&lt;/tt&gt; return true when we go from having to not having the DENSE flag. It should be pretty easy to validate a fix with a small addition to &lt;tt&gt;CompactTableTest&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
